{
  "stem": "166.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 21.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Finally, they went to the Jewish, the Jewish community center there, and they demanded that they should give so many thousands of people to be transported, to be evacuated.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "We did not know where they going to evacuate them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We did not know that they take them to Auschwitz, and they're going to gas them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We thought--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandfather from-- my mother's father-- died when he was 57 years old, so he died before the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father's father was also in Bedzin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were still there, but I was-- that's what I'm coming to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the Jewish community-- they made a, a special Jewish police because we were had to live on one part of side of the city.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We could not go on the streets, on the main streets, anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We, we lived on the side of the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were Jewish police, where they was wearing white hats and a blue stripe around, and also a Jewish band with a Jewish blue star on it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Later there came an order that we had to wear a yellow star on the, on the front, on the chest.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, because they didn't trust-- because they didn't trust that some people took off the armband, and then they went on the Aryan side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, so we had to wear a Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Two weeks later, a month later, we had to cut out a hole in the nicest suits that we had, and put the yellow star behind it, and sew it around so you cannot tear it off again, to make it sure for themselves.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In order to not to go to camp-- because they came with special commanders on the streets-- they came, maybe a few thousand soldiers.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
